    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your<strong> white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>remaining Italian hard cheese</strong> and <strong>chopped chives</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Peel and grate your <strong>garlic</strong> into the bowl (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and mix to combine – this is your <strong>Caesar dressing</strong></p>",
